This presentation focuses on Digital Literacy for Students - highlighting the essential skills required to effectively use digital technologies in today’s world. It explains what digital literacy is including the ability to access, evaluate, and use online information safely and responsibly.
The presentation also emphasizes the importance of maintaining a professional online presence, following safe internet practices and protecting personal data. Additionally, it introduces useful digital tools that can enhance learning and productivity.
Overall, the presentation aims to help students become responsible, informed, and confident digital users.
